{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κατα-ψύχω</b> [ῡ], <br /> <b>cool, chill</b>, ὕδωρ κ. τὴν ξηρὰν ἀναθυμίασιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 361a2, compare 368b34; ὁ φόβος καταψύχει [prev. author] “PA” 650b28, compare “Pr.” 954b13, +others\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; αἱ ἄτομοι.. κατέψυξαν [τὸ σῶμα] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 60 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> - ψῠγήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Vettius Valens Astrologus 73.21 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> -έψυγμαι: <i>aorist</i> -εψύχθην, also -εψύγην [ῠ] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 897a22 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>to be chilled, become cold</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἀφορισμοί” 4.40, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 531b31, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of persons, κατεψυγμένοι, opposed to θερμοί, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Rh.” 1389b30. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, οὐ -έψυξαν τὴν ὁρμήν <b>did</b> not <b>allow</b> their ardour <b>to cool</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Bellum Judaicum” 1.2.7 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]:— <i>passive</i>, κατέψυκτο τὸ πρακτικόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pompeius” 46, compareCritodem. in “Cat.Codex Astr.” 8(1).259, Vett.Val. [prev. cited]\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>] <br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>cool, refresh</b>, καταψύχει πνοή [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 127. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>dry</b> land after irrigation, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PCair.Zen.” 155 (3rd c.BC):\">Refs